title: Commercial property market value in the United Kingdom ( UK ) 2012 to 2016
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Market value in billion GBP, with a total of 5 data points. The chart has 2 significant trends.
The longest trend is extremely positive which exists from 2015 to 2012.
Additionally, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2016 to 2015.
gold: This statistic illustrates the value of the commercial property market in the United Kingdom ( UK ) from 2012 to 2016 . It can be seen that in 2016 the commercial property market reached a value of 883 billion British pounds .
